Title : [Myofibrosis in childhood. Differential diagnosis in chest pain].
Date : 1993
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : It is emphasised in connection with the differential diagnosis of chest complaints that after excluded the serious and urgent conditions, a searching for painful muscle bundles and trigger points at the characteristic locations in the muscles can explain the origin of the complaints. By finding of myofibrosis, other expensive or invasive diagnostic tests can be omitted and the patient gets rid off his or her claims.
